    "created_at": "2015-03-29T22:18:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-29T22:18:30Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I spent some time looking at this today and think we need to step back a bit:\n- Remove the call to register_events on the entire toolbar.\n- Remove most of the calls to focus_cell that were added in the actions.js PR. The only calls to focus_cell should be the ones that were in the original keyboard manager. The actions.js PR included a number of new calls to focus cell that don't belong there.\n- Audit the code base for other calls to focus_cell and remove ones that are not there for good reason.\n\nBasically I think we need to go back to where things were closer to the 2.0 release. I recall that all of the problems we now have are _new_ since then. What @jdfreder and I found when we were writing all of the keyboard handling stuff is that there should be almost no calls to focus_cell - everytime we tried to put one in somewhere it lead to these problems. The calls we had in the 2.0 release were highly tuned and well understood.\n"
  },
