    "body": "I am fine putting register events on specific limited elements in the\ntoolbar such as the cell type selector that have their own keyboard\nshortcuts. I will give #8191 a shot...\n\nOn Sun, Mar 29, 2015 at 4:58 PM, Min RK notifications@github.com wrote:\n\n> Remove the call to register_events on the entire toolbar.\n> \n> This means that elements in the toolbar can be focused (e.g. cell type\n> select), where keyboard actions make sense, but will actually be triggering\n> shortcuts. We added the call because this behavior was confusing.\n> \n> @ellisonbg https://github.com/ellisonbg I've opened #8191\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/pull/8191 with the first two of your\n> bullets. Can you test that one out, and identify specifically what problems\n> remain that we should fix for 3.1?\n> \n> â€”\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/8054#issuecomment-87499183.\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\n@ellisonbg on Twitter and GitHub\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
